How to use the app?

1. Download and install all the necessary requirements from requirements.txt. Write in the command line:
    "pip3 install -r requirements.txt"
2. Download "app" folder and all of the files within, as well as other files - .flaskenv, config.py, library.py
3. Initialize database from command line:
    "flask db init"
    The default db file will be created as "booklibrary.db"
4. To prepare migration of the db, use "flask db migrate", to complete it - "flask db upgrade"
    Migrations history will be available in "migrations" folder
5. To open the shell in the command line, use:
    flask shell